    "industrial_process_notes": "Not industrially polymerized -- biosynthesized in plant cell walls and obtained as a byproduct of kraft and sulfite chemical pulping (delignification) in the paper industry. The Swiss botanist A. P. de Candolle first described lignin in 1813, naming it from the Latin 'lignum' (wood); it is the third most abundant natural polymer after cellulose and chitin.",
